text.tspan: Total fertility rate versus shifted cohort fertility rate, Sweden

Two measures of fertility rate are compared: the
total fertility rate
(a summary metric based on birth rates

across different age groups of women in one particular year) and the
completed cohort fertility rate
(the
average number of children born to a woman by the end of her childbearing years).
Data source: HFD; Human Fertility Database (2024)
Note: The completed cohort fertility rate is typically given by the woman's birth year. In this chart, it has been shifted +30 years to see how the
two measures compare at roughly the average age of mothers at childbirth.
